.TH "PAGEREVEALEVENT.VIEWTRANSITION" "3JS" "November 6, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
PageRevealEvent.viewTransition \- PageRevealEvent: viewTransition
property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]viewTransition\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]PageRevealEvent\f[R] interface contains a
\f[CR]ViewTransition\f[R] object representing the active view transition
for the cross\-document navigation.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The active view transition can also be accessed via the
\f[CR]Document.activeViewTransition\f[R] property.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]ViewTransition\f[R] object, or \f[CR]null\f[R] if no view
transition is active when the event is fired.
.SH EXAMPLES
See the main \f[CR]PageRevealEvent\f[R] page.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
Navigation API
.IP \(bu 2
View Transition API
